'07-06-YYYY' : '<a href="#"><div class="question"><div class="questioncontainer">Wage = Number of hours of overtime × £15 + Basic pay</div><div class="questiontext"><p>A person’s weekly wage is worked out using the formula above. (i) Find a person’s Wage when the Number of hours of overtime is 7 and the Basic pay is £150. (ii) Find the Number of hours of overtime, when the Wage is £270 and the Basic pay is £180.</p></div></div><div class="answer"><div class="answercontainer">Wage = Number of hours of overtime × £15 + Basic pay</div><div class="answertext"><p>(a) 7 x 15 + 150  =255 (b) 270 = ? X 15 + 180, 270 - 180 = ? X 15, 90 = ? X 15, ? = 90÷15=6</p></div></div></a>',
